Boundaries:  When to Say Yes, When to Say No||<p><b>Dates:&nbsp;&nbsp;  April 7 - May 26, 2010<br> Material Fee:&nbsp; $12.00 includes participant  workbook<br> Course Instructor:&nbsp; Amanda M. Allen, M.A.&nbsp; ~ New Day  Counseling</b></p><p><i>Boundaries </i>is a unique journey --- of spiritual growth, of  challenge to change, of problem solving, of recovery, of hope.&nbsp; Offering  practical help and encouragement to all who seek a healthy, balance  life, Boundaries presents insight and wisdom for those seeking to deal  with their inability to say no.</p><p>This 8-week series is based on the best seller, <i>Boundaries ---  When to Say Yes, When to Say No, to Take Control of Your Life</i>, by  Dr. Henry Cloud and Dr. John Townsend.&nbsp; These interactive 8-week  sessions present the importance of developing healthy boundaries in  order to maintain healthy relationships.&nbsp; This course is for those  already in healthy situations who would like to have a better sense of  &ldquo;yes&rdquo; and &rdquo;no,&rdquo; as well as those who are in great need of setting  healthy boundaries.</p><p><a target="_blank" href="https://secure.accessacs.com/access/nonmemberlogin.aspx?ReturnUrl=events%2fwz_people.aspx&amp;ChurchID=3183&amp;EventID=12597&amp;sn=1233">Register for Boundaries Class</a></p><hr><h2>Course Facilitator:</h2><h3><img style="border: 0pt none; float: left; padding-right: 15px; padding-bottom: 15px;" title="GRAPHIC : Life Learning : Teacher Photo :  Amanda Allen : JPG - Boundaries, Cloud and Townsend" alt="GRAPHIC : Life  Learning : Teacher Photo : Amanda Allen : JPG - Boundaries, Cloud and  Townsend" src="http://www.pcctoday.com/monkimage.php?mediaDirectory=mediafiles&amp;mediaId=455455&amp;fileName=graphic--life-learning--teacher-photo--amanda-allen--jpg-0-0-175-263.jpg" height="263" width="175">Amanda M. Allen, M.A.</h3><p><b>New Day Counseling</b><br><a target="_blank" href="http://newdaycounseling.com/">http://newdaycounseling.com</a></p><p><b>BIOGRAPHY:</b><br>I received my Master's&nbsp;degree&nbsp;in Counseling from  George Fox University&nbsp;in Portland, OR, and a Bachelor&rsquo;s degree from  Vanguard University in Southern California. My training has been in both  individual and couples counseling. I was a licensed minister for seven  years. I am&nbsp;registered&nbsp;with the Oregon Board&nbsp;of Licensed Professional  Counselors and Therapists.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>I specialize in counseling&nbsp;children 11 years old and up. My passion  is working with young adults and those&nbsp;going through life transitions  and relationship issues.&nbsp;I have&nbsp;been trained in Sand Tray therapy, and  I&nbsp;am&nbsp;certified to give the Prepared and Enrich pre-married assessment  test.</p><p>I enjoy living in the Northwest and exploring its beauty.&nbsp;Some of  my&nbsp;interests include photography,&nbsp;the Portland Trail Blazers and college  football. I enjoy being a wife and spending quality time with family  and friends.</p>